# Todo API REST Client

### Get all todos
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/todos \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json"

### Create new todo
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/todos \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{
        "description": "Learn Spring Boot",
        "creationDate": "2024-03-14T10:00:00",
        "expirationDate": "2024-03-20T18:00:00",
        "category": "LEARNING",
        "state": "ACTIVE"
    }'

### Update existing todo (replace {id} with actual todo id)
curl -X PUT http://localhost:8080/todos/1 \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{
        "description": "Learn Spring Boot - Updated",
        "creationDate": "2024-03-14T10:00:00",
        "expirationDate": "2024-03-20T18:00:00",
        "category": "LEARNING",
        "state": "DONE"
    }'

### Get OpenAPI definition
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/v3/api-docs \
    -H "Accept: application/json"

